## Source Code Workspace

- `WORKSPACE_PATH` is this agent's private operating workspace.
- `CODE_WORKSPACE_ROOT` is the board's shared source-code area.
- `CODE_WORKTREE_PATH` is the git worktree this agent should use for implementation work.
- If `CODE_REPO_URL` is blank, use runtime `REPO_URL` if it exists.
- Before changing a task that requires code, verify `CODE_WORKTREE_PATH` is a git worktree. If it is missing and no repo URL/credential is available, add a task comment with the exact blocker.

## Notes

- Required tools: `curl`, `jq`

## OpenAPI refresh (run before API-heavy work)

```bash
mkdir -p api
curl -fsS "{{ base_url }}/openapi.json" -o api/openapi.json
jq -r '
  .paths | to_entries[] as $p
  | $p.value | to_entries[]
  | select((.value.tags // []) | index("{{ role_tag }}"))
  | "\(.key|ascii_upcase)\t\($p.key)\t\(.value.operationId // "-")\t\(.value[\"x-llm-intent\"] // "-")\t\(.value[\"x-when-to-use\"] // [] | join(\" | \"))\t\(.value[\"x-routing-policy\"] // [] | join(\" | \"))"
' api/openapi.json | sort > api/{{ role_tag }}-operations.tsv
```

## API source of truth
- `api/openapi.json`
- `api/{{ role_tag }}-operations.tsv`
  - Columns: METHOD, PATH, OP_ID, X_LLM_INTENT, X_WHEN_TO_USE, X_ROUTING_POLICY

## API discovery policy
- Use operations tagged `{{ role_tag }}`.
- Prefer operations whose `x-llm-intent` and `x-when-to-use` match the current objective.
- Derive method/path/schema from `api/openapi.json` at runtime.
- Do not hardcode endpoint paths in markdown files.

## API safety
If no confident match exists for current intent, ask one clarifying question.


## Charts (built-in MCP App)

You can render interactive charts directly in any {{ product_name }} chat surface
(board chat, group chat, channel threads, planning chat) by posting a memory
entry with `content_type: "mcp_app_result"` and `app_metadata.app: "chart"`.

### Supported chart types

| `type`   | Description                                                |
|----------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `line`   | Line chart — burndowns, trends, cumulative flow            |
| `area`   | Area (filled) chart — velocity, throughput over time       |
| `bar`    | Bar chart — workload by agent, task counts, comparisons    |
| `pie`    | Pie chart — status breakdown, priority split               |
| `donut`  | Donut chart — same as pie, with a centred value label      |

### Chart spec

```json
{
  "type":   "<line|area|bar|pie|donut>",
  "title":  "<optional heading shown above chart>",
  "xKey":   "<field name used as X axis or pie label>",
  "yKeys":  "<field name, or array of field names, for Y values>",
  "xLabel": "<optional X axis label>",
  "yLabel": "<optional Y axis label>",
  "data":   [ { "<xKey>": "...", "<yKey>": 0 } ],
  "colors": ["<optional hex or CSS colour overrides, one per series>"],
  "height": 260
}
```

Required: `type`, `xKey`, `yKeys`, `data`. All `yKeys` values must be numbers.
Limit `data` to ≤ 500 rows — aggregate larger datasets before charting.

### Posting a chart
{% if board_id is defined and board_id %}
Board chat:
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/memory" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Sprint burndown for current sprint.",
    "tags": ["chat"],
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "app_metadata": {
      "app": "chart",
      "spec": {
        "type": "line",
        "title": "Sprint Burndown",
        "xKey": "day",
        "yKeys": ["remaining", "ideal"],
        "data": [
          {"day": "Mon", "remaining": 24, "ideal": 20},
          {"day": "Fri", "remaining":  4, "ideal":  4}
        ]
      }
    }
  }'
```

Group chat (via board context):
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/group-memory" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Team velocity this quarter.",
    "tags": ["chat"],
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "app_metadata": {
      "app": "chart",
      "spec": { "type": "bar", "xKey": "agent", "yKeys": ["tasks"], "data": [...] }
    }
  }'
```
{% endif %}
Channel thread:
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/threads/{thread_id}/messages" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Deployment timeline.",
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "event_metadata": {
      "app": "chart",
      "spec": { "type": "area", "xKey": "sprint", "yKeys": ["completed", "committed"], "data": [...] }
    }
  }'
```

### Chart data sources
{% if board_id is defined and board_id %}
Always query the API for real data — never fabricate values.

| Data needed | API path |
|---|---|
| Task list with statuses | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/tasks` |
| Sprint list | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/sprints` |
| Sprint tickets and estimates | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/sprints/{sprint_id}/tickets` |
| Board activity events | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/activity` |
| Velocity & estimation accuracy | `GET /api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/velocity` |

For velocity charts, use `estimate_minutes` and `actual_minutes` from sprint
tickets or the velocity endpoint. Aggregate and convert to hours where helpful.
{% endif %}
